Rajasthan Royals have stumbled to just 151 for 9 in Guwahati after a fiery power-play start. Moeen Ali and Varun Chakaravarthy spun a web to trigger a collapse as RR crumbled from 67 for 1 to 82 for 5. Only Jurel and Archer provided late resistance but it was too little on a decent batting track. KKR will be the happier side and should fancy chasing this total with ease.
